@@TJvUnInstaller.DeleteFromScript@string
Description:
Call this method to delete files/registry entries defined in a script. The script must be an ascii text and must be compliant with the following format:

TYPE:VALUE 
The type can be DIRECTORY FILE REGISTRY-KEY REGISTRY-VALUE SHARED and the uninstaller will handle correctly any of these type. Be sure of adding the line with the directory after the files included in the directory.

DIRECTORY: the entry is a directory 
FILE: the entry is a standard file 
REGISTRY-KEY: the entry is a key in the registry 
REGISTRY-VALUE: the entry is a value in a registry key 
SHARED: the value is a shared file

Example: 
FILE:c:Program FilesTestFile1.exe 
DIRECTORY:c:Program FilesTest

Bad example: 
DIRECTORY:c:Program FilesTest 
FILE:c:Program FilesTestFile1.exe

